<TITLE> Explosion at Valero's Houston refinery: local TV </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 HOUSTON, Mon Aug 4,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Firefighters and hazardous materials crews responded to an explosion Monday morning at Valero's 130,000 barrel per day Houston refinery, according to KHOU-TV. Valero representatives were unavailable for comment. A local telephone service that warns residents near Houston's refinery row of problems said there had been an "incident" at the refinery causing sulfur fumes to be released from a sulfur tank. A shelter-in-place order for residents in the Manchester neighborhood of Houston was ordered by the Houston fire department, KHOU reported. A spokeswoman for the Houston Fire Department said she didn't have information immediately available about the incident. The television station showed video of a smoldering tank at the refinery in a Monday morning news report. Debris could be seen on the ground near the tank
